<h1>Shrimp and Sirloin Sizzle</h1>

Yield: 4-6 servings

1  pound  boneless top sirloin steak, cut into thin, 2-inch-long strips<br/>
1/3  cup  fresh lime juice<br/>
3  tablespoons  hoisin sauce<br/>
2  tablespoons  grated fresh ginger<br/>
1  tablespoon  honey<br/>
1  tablespoon  soy sauce<br/>
1/2  teaspoon  dried crushed red pepper<br/>
1  teaspoon  vegetable oil<br/>
1  pound  shrimp, peeled and deveined<br/>
1/2  red bell pepper, thinly sliced<br/>
1/2  yellow bell pepper, thinly sliced<br/>
Hot cooked rice<br/>

Garnish: sliced green onion

1. Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl; toss to coat.

2. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet or wok over medium-high heat
until hot. Add steak and marinade to pan; cook 3 minutes or to desired
degree of doneness. Add shrimp and bell peppers, and cook, stirring
constantly, 3 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink. Serve
immediately over hot cooked rice. Garnish, if desired.

Notes (Mom): You can make this with just shrimp, or just steak, or even chicken.